# Code style

## No console in code

Do **not** write `console.log`, `console.error`, `console.warn`, `console.info`, `console.debug` or any other `console.*` in source code.

Remove or replace with proper logging/error handling if needed.

## Single-line if without braces

When an `if` (or `else if`) has only one statement and fits on one line, write it **without** curly braces.

- **Good:** `if (x) return`
- **Good:** `if (!ok) throw new Error('fail')`
- **Good:** `if (condition) doSomething()`
- **Bad:** `if (x) { return }`
- **Bad:** `if (!ok) { throw new Error('fail') }`

Use braces when the body has multiple statements or spans more than one line.
